other_tests.findings: Atrophy of the bilateral frontal and temporal lobes with parietal and occipital sparing, hypertrophic astrogliosis within the superficial and deep white matter, loss of axonal processes with secondary myelin loss and prominent axonal spheroids, no inflammation seen.
No evidence of cerebral autosomal dominant arteriopathy with subcortical infarcts and leukoencephalopathy.
Initial MDRS score of 130/144 and decline noted over time.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Decline in cognitive function noted over 3 years with the final MDRS score of 123/144.
